@page "/help/contributing"

<PageTitle>Contributing to TheDiscDb</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="Learn how to contribute disc data to TheDiscDb, from identifying a release to submitting playlists for review." />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://thediscdb.com/help/contributing" />
</HeadContent>

<TheDiscDb.Client.Controls.Breadcrumb PrimaryText="Contributing" Items='[("Home", "/"), ("About", "/about")]' />

<div class="contribute-layout help-page">
    <div class="page-header">
        <h1>Contributing to <span class="page-header__accent">TheDiscDb</span></h1>
        <div class="page-header__sub">
            Help improve the database by sharing verified disc layouts with the community.
        </div>
    </div>

    <section class="info-card">
        <h2>What contributing means</h2>
        <p>
            A contribution adds release and disc structure data that helps other collectors identify the
            right playlists in MakeMKV without guessing.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="info-grid">
        <article class="info-card">
            <h2>What you’ll need</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>A computer with a compatible disc drive.</li>
                <li><a href="https://www.makemkv.com/download/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MakeMKV</a> installed.</li>
                <li>Chrome or Edge for the upload helper flow.</li>
                <li>A GitHub account for sign-in and attribution.</li>
                <li>Release details like UPC, ASIN, and release date.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="info-card">
            <h2>How it works</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Identify the release with TMDB search or ID.</li>
                <li>Add release details and cover images.</li>
                <li>Upload MakeMKV scan logs for each disc.</li>
                <li>Label disc titles and submit for review.</li>
            </ol>
        </article>
    </section>

    <section class="info-card">
        <h2>What happens after submission</h2>
        <p>
            Submissions go through review, then approved entries are added to the public database with
            contributor attribution.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-0">
            Prefer automation? Engram can pre-capture disc logs before you continue in the standard
            contribution flow.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="callout">
        <h3>Ready to contribute?</h3>
        <p>Start the contribution flow and we’ll guide you through each step.</p>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contribute">Go to Contribute</a>
    </section>
</div>
